Mary of Teck:
&quot;Mary of Teck (Victoria Mary Augusta Louise Olga Pauline Claudine Agnes; 26 May 1867 – 24 March 1953) was Queen consort of the United Kingdom and the British Dominions, and Empress consort of India, as the wife of King-Emperor George V.&quot;
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_of_Teck" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_of_Teck</a>

This photo appeared in The Sunday Oregonian, September 30, 1917, SECTION FIVE, Image 70 with the caption:
&quot;When King George, Queen Mary and the Crown Prince visited the Tommies fighting on the western front in France, demonstrations of the new methods of attack only recently introduced were given for their benefit. A liquid fire or flame-throwing attack was shown so that the royal visitors could get an idea of this latest war weapon. The royal visitors were greatly impressed by all they saw. It was the first visit that Queen Mary had paid to the Tommies fighting in France and they cheered her continuously whenever the opportunity presented itself.&quot;
<a href="http://oregonnews.uoregon.edu/lccn/sn83045782/1917-09-30/ed-1/seq-70/" rel="nofollow">oregonnews.uoregon.edu/lccn/sn83045782/1917-09-30/ed-1/se...</a>

