The Sunday Oregonian, August 05, 1917, SECTION FIVE, Image 71 published this photo with the caption:
&quot;An American railroad man is now at the head of the British Admiralty. At least Sir Eric Geddes, who has just been named for this responsible position, was trained in railroading in America and his knowledge was utilized by Kitchener in organizing transportation at the beginning of the war. He was knighted a year ago. Now he is first Lord of the Admiralty and is giving special attention to the submarine situation.&quot;
