More on the camp from the New York Times&quot;

&quot;BOYS FOR TRAINING CAMP.; Commission Announces Names of First Group from Metropolis.

May 21, 1917,

ALBANY, May 20.--The first group of boys from Manhattan, the Bronx, and Brooklyn to attend the State Training Camp at Peekskill during July has been selected by the Military Training Commission. It was announced that 900 boys from Greater New York will be sent to the camp and an equal number from up-State communities.&quot;
