&quot;Lieutenant H. A. Seeley, of the &quot;Kilties,&quot; now in this country, was a bank manager in Western Canada when the war broke out. He resigned and en listed as a private. He has seen eight months in the trenches. When injured by a shell while carrying a wounded officer on his shoulder, he was recommended for a commission and invalided home.&quot;
