This photo ran in The Sunday Oregonian. (Portland, Ore.) 1881-current, July 29, 1917, SECTION FIVE, Image 59 with the caption:
&quot;The Wilbur Wright Aviation camp is one of the biggest aviation schools in the United States and in the world. It has just been completed and made ready for the reception of hundreds of men learning to fly for Uncle Sam. The school is named after the great pioneer of flying, the late Wilbur Wright. The field is 2500 acres in area and has accommodations for 800 air planes and 1500 students. Two squadrons are on the field today. Two more will be formed.&quot;
